[1] What data do we collect?
<Data managed by our company>
User ID (value generated upon app launch)
Operating system name and version
Device name
Device language setting
App version number
App progress (scores, reached levels, ranking data, etc.)
App operation status (data for analysis such as pressed buttons and displayed screens)
Player data (nickname, login, in-app purchases, etc.)
IP address (only as a log of the web server, not linked with the User ID)
Date and time of transmission and reception
*Supplement
As listed, our company does not collect any personally identifiable information (such as name, date of birth, address, phone number, email address, ID number, detailed location data, hereafter referred to as "personal information").
The User ID is a value used to link app data with the server, and a different value is assigned to each app. There is no regularity or association with other services.。
<Information obtained through services operated by third parties>
Advertising ID (when consent is obtained from the user)
For iOS devices, it's called IDFA (Identifier For Advertising)
For Android OS devices, it's called AAID (Google Advertising ID)
IP address (which may be used for rough location estimation)
Country
User operations and interactions (app launch, taps, video viewing, etc.)
Information about ad display (number of ad displays, number of clicks, etc.)
Diagnostic information (crash logs, app launch time, hang-up rate, energy consumption, etc.)
Payer information (for those who make in-app purchases, including the country, region, and currency of the payer)
Date and time of transmission and reception
*Supplement
The third-party services are app distribution store operators (Apple for the App Store, Google for Google Play), and ad delivery operators. (For details, see
[2]
)
While app distribution store operators handle personal information, the use of our app does not mean that we can obtain personal information of the user.
Ad delivery operators may handle personal information in other services they provide, but the use of our app does not mean that we can obtain personal information of the user.
In other words, we do not obtain personal information from services operated by third parties.
The Advertising ID is a unique value on the device. If the user permits, it can span other services, and based on the information obtained from other services, we may customize and deliver ads in our app for you. You can change the Advertising ID at any time, and you can also opt out in the OS settings.
