[3] How do we collect your data?
Our company collects your data when you use our smartphone app through communication over the internet between your device and our management server.
We may also indirectly receive your data from the third-party services listed in
[2].
For the handling of data, please refer to the privacy policy of each company. (For details about the third-party services, please refer to
[2].
)
[4] How will we use your data?
We collect your data so that we can:
Provide the features of our smartphone app
Maintain, protect, and improve our smartphone app
Check the usage status of our smartphone app
Respond to inquiries about our smartphone app
Respond to acts that violate our terms and other regulations regarding our smartphone app
Create statistical data about usage status
Deliver advertisements in our smartphone app
Understand the status of ad delivery and measure the effectiveness of ads
Plan, propose, and implement new services in the future
Provide some information to the third-party services that we use
*Supplement
We will not disclose your data without your consent. Data for rankings (scores and nicknames) and online matches (nicknames, ratings, etc.) are disclosed as they are intended to be seen by others. However, even in such cases, personal information will not be identified.
[5] How do we store your data?
The data handled by our smartphone app is stored as a data file in the app data area inside the device you use. Normally, access to this data file is not possible except by the app itself. (Of course, the OS can access it, and people who can use the device can also access it.) A part of the created data and the device information obtainable from the app are transmitted to our management server via encrypted communication (SSL), and stored on our management server.
Our management server utilizes a paid rental server provided within Japan. The location of the server is Japan. As the company providing the rental server is responsible for security, security measures are perfect.
The storage period of data on the management server is as long as the corresponding app is providing its service. For apps that have ended their service, the data will be deleted within one year.
As for the data within the device, all will be deleted when the app is uninstalled. However, data linked to the store's account (for example, non-consumable in-app purchases, backed-up app data) may be restored when the app is reinstalled.
The data provided to services operated by third parties will be handled according to their privacy policies.
*Supplement
In our smartphone app, most data is stored inside the device. For example, player data such as the progress of a game app is stored within the device. On our management server, we handle log data, such as user behavior history. However, in features such as ranking displays, user scores and the nicknames you set are stored on our management server.
Even if you uninstall the app, your data on our management server will not be deleted. This is because we cannot obtain information that the app has been uninstalled. If you wish to delete this, please refer to
[7]
.
[6] Marketing
We do not use the data we manage for marketing purposes.
However, the data provided to services operated by third parties may be used by those organizations.
[7] What are your data protection rights?
Our Company would like to make sure you are fully aware of all of your data protection rights. Every user is entitled to the following:
The right to access - You have the right to request Our Company for copies of your personal data. We may charge you a small fee for this service.
The right to rectification - You have the right to request that Our Company correct any information you believe is inaccurate. You also have the right to request Our Company to complete the information you believe is incomplete.
The right to erasure - You have the right to request that Our Company erase your personal data, under certain conditions.
The right to restrict processing - You have the right to request that Our Company restrict the processing of your personal data, under certain conditions.
The right to object to processing - You have the right to object to Our Company’s processing of your personal data, under certain conditions.
The right to data portability - You have the right to request that Our Company transfer the data that we have collected to another organization, or directly to you, under certain conditions.
We will respond to your requests within one month. If you want to exercise any of these rights, please contact us (see
[14]
). When doing so, be sure to provide the name of the relevant app and the user ID displayed on the screen. Also, you may be asked to provide some information for the purpose of verifying whether the personal data is yours.
[8] What are cookies?
Cookies are text files placed on your computer to collect standard Internet log information and visitor behavior information. When you visit our websites, we may collect information from you automatically through cookies or similar technology
For further information, visit allaboutcookies.org.
[9] How do we use cookies?
We do not use cookies. However, due to the nature of the app, data is stored on your device. If you cannot accept this, you will not be able to use the app's functions.
Also, services operated by third parties may use cookies. They are handled according to their privacy policy.
[10] What types of cookies do we use?
We do not use cookies. It's the same as
[9]
.
[11] How to manage your cookies
We do not use cookies. It's the same as
[9]
.
[12] Privacy policies of other websites
Our smartphone app may contain links to other websites. However, this privacy policy only applies to our smartphone app, so when you move to a different website, please read their privacy policy. For our website, please refer to
this privacy policy
.
[13] Changes to our privacy policy
We regularly review our privacy policy and post updates on this webpage.
The last update to this privacy policy was on July 12, 2023.
